<item>
            <title>[DERBY-1117] SQLException can lose  stacktrace in some cases.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1117</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;cause is being lost in the following constructor in SqlException&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   public SqlException(LogWriter logwriter,&lt;br/&gt;
       MessageId msgid, Object[] args, Throwable cause)&lt;/p&gt;
   {
       this(
           logwriter,
           msgutil_.getCompleteMessage(
               msgid.msgid,
               args),
           ExceptionUtil.getSQLStateFromIdentifier(msgid.msgid),
           ExceptionUtil.getSeverityFromIdentifier(msgid.msgid));
   }

&lt;p&gt;maybe we should add setThrowable(cause) so we dont lose track of it.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
